<br>
 And of those which is particularly useful at the highend raids and unique? Sneak and hide used to be useful for CR, now that's pretty much monk domain. Hide = Evade. Disarm? Pickpocket? Taunt? I had to get 23aa points to get a taunt that actually works on raid mobs, and that's on a 15 minute recycle.<br>
<br>
 As for this horrible monk-wrecking ability: As a MT the reason I'd really want this is just to avoid some riposte damage. But unless it goes so far as to completely negate mob ripostes/dodges/parries I seriously doubt it will allow warriors to pass monks in frontal damage. And even then...seeing as how my DPS seems to hover around 50ish on low AC mobs, from behind. While our similarly equipped monks are in the 100dps range. So unless mob defensive abilities are negating fully half of our damage(haven't personally tested to see if they are) I don't think that my monkeys are in any serious jeopardy. Parses I've seen from other guilds show similar numbers. <br>
<br>
 That all said, I could care less if monks get these abilities. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=6122" target="_blank">
